# Windows XP 64-Bit Retro Gaming Build

This machine is part of my personal retro PC project, tailored for running Windows XP 32-Bit-era titles at native performance on real hardware. Itâ€™s built with performance and compatibility in mind for early 2000s gaming.

## History


---

## Mission Statement

To create a PC that runs games that have mid era EAX, lack 64-bit support or make use of Table Fog, Paletted Textures or EMBM at a target resolution of 1024x768.

